Problem is that the `Cookie` object returned is **nullable**.

Options:

1. try/catch - try to check if the cookie exists
             - catch `NullPointerException` and try again 

2. create a retryable method that accepts another returning method (Supplier) and evaluates the boolean expression (Predicate) you want met.   *recommended

For example:

      public &lt;T&gt; boolean retryable(Supplier&lt;T&gt; method, Predicate&lt;T&gt; condition, int retries) {
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; retries; i++) {
          T methodReturnValue = method.get();
          if (!condition.test(methodReturnValue) || methodReturnValue == null) {
            // Todo: sleep / wait / try again immediately
          } else {
              return true;
          }
        }
        return false;
      }


**Just implicitly waiting without retrying is not recommended as it can waste execution time that builds up for each test using this wait**

